# 🚀 PHASE 2 — EXPANSION SYSTEMS

## 🧟 Zombie Survival (2.5D)

---

# 🎯 1. Purpose

Define all systems that are:

* NOT part of MVP
* BUT part of long-term vision
* Derived from previous repos and missing ideas

---

# 🧠 2. Core Philosophy

> Phase 2 adds depth without breaking the simplicity of the core loop.

---

# ⚠️ 3. Rule

Do NOT implement these until:

* MVP is fully playable
* Game feel is polished
* Core loop is stable

---

# 🧩 4. Phase 2 System Overview

This phase introduces:

* Room / map progression
* Mission system
* Advanced combat mechanics
* Environment system
* Tutorial / onboarding
* Game modes expansion
* Hub / meta UX layer
* Audio & visual systems
* (Future) Multiplayer (archived)

---

# 🗺️ 5. Room / Map Progression

## Concept

Instead of one static arena:

* player unlocks new areas during run

---

## Features

* locked areas
* unlock cost (currency or condition)
* different room layouts
* difficulty scaling per room

---

## Gameplay Effect

* creates decision-making
* breaks monotony
* adds spatial progression

---

# 🎯 6. Mission System

## Concept

Give players objectives beyond survival.

---

## Examples

* kill 100 zombies
* survive 5 minutes
* defeat boss
* use specific weapon

---

## Types

* in-run missions
* meta missions (across runs)

---

## Reward

* bonus currency
* unlock items
* XP boost

---

# 🔫 7. Advanced Combat Mechanics

## Add Later

* reload system
* weapon switching
* manual aiming (optional)
* sprint

---

## Purpose

* increase skill ceiling
* add player control depth

---

## Rule

Only add after base combat is stable.

---

# 🌍 8. Environment System

## Concept

Environment becomes part of gameplay.

---

## Features

* different map themes
* visual patterns
* hazards (optional)
* interactive elements (later)

---

## Examples

* slow zones
* damage zones
* obstacle layouts

---

# 🎓 9. Tutorial / Onboarding

## Purpose

Help new players understand:

* movement
* shooting
* upgrade system
* UI navigation

---

## Implementation

* first-time tutorial
* tooltips
* guided steps

---

# 🧭 10. Hub / Meta Layer

## Concept

Add a layer outside gameplay.

---

## Features

* main hub screen
* access:

  * hero select
  * weapon select
  * upgrades
  * missions

---

## Purpose

* make game feel like a full product
* centralize progression

---

# 🎮 11. Game Modes Expansion

## New Modes

* Endless mode
* Challenge mode
* Boss rush

---

## Purpose

* increase replayability
* create different experiences

---

# 🔊 12. Audio & Feedback Systems

## Systems

* audio manager
* hit sounds
* ambient sounds
* UI sounds

---

## Visual

* particle system
* animation system
* shader effects

---

## Purpose

* improve game feel
* increase immersion

---

# ⚙️ 13. Performance System

## Features

* optimize enemy count
* manage effects
* maintain FPS

---

## Purpose

* ensure mobile performance

---

# 🌐 14. Multiplayer (Future / Archived)

## Concept

* co-op survival
* shared combat

---

## Status

* NOT for current development
* keep as future idea only

---

# 🧠 15. Integration Strategy

## Order

1. Mission system
2. Room progression
3. Environment system
4. Advanced combat
5. Hub layer
6. Game modes
7. Audio/visual polish

---

# ⚠️ 16. What NOT to Do

Do NOT:

* implement all systems at once
* break MVP simplicity
* overdesign early

---

# 🎯 17. Success Criteria

Phase 2 is successful when:

* gameplay feels deeper
* replayability increases
* systems integrate cleanly
* performance remains stable

---

# 🧠 Final Principle

> Expand carefully. Never break the core loop.

